ar||LGBT, Politics||Rites Publishing, non-profit collective  ||\n|-\n|''[[Room (magazine)|Room]]''|| || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]''|| || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Rue Morgue (magazine)|Rue Morgue]]''||1997||||English||||horror in culture and entertainment||[[Rodrigo Gudi\u00f1o]]  ||\n|-\n|''[[Ryerson Review of Journalism]]'' || 1984 ||  || English || || personalities and issues in journalism || [[Ryerson University]] School of Journalism ||  \n|-\n|''[[Saskatchewan History]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Saturday Night (magazine)|Saturday Night]]'' || 1887 || 2005 ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[SAY (magazine)|SAY]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Scoregolf]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[S\u00e9quences]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Shameless (magazine)|Shameless]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Sharp (magazine)|Sharp]]''||2008||||English||Bi-monthly||Men's||Contempo Media Inc.  ||\n|-\n|''[[Shift (magazine)|Shift]]''||1992||2003||English||Monthly, later bi-monthly||Technology, culture||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Sir John Magazine]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Siren (magazine)|Siren]]'' || 1995 || 2004 ||English|| Bimonthly || Lesbian culture, news in Toronto ||   ||\n|-\n|''[[Spacing (magazine)|Spacing]]'' || 2003 || ||English|| Quarterly || Urban affairs || Spacing Media || \n|-\n|''[[Sportsnet Magazine]]''|| 2011 ||  || English || Bi-weekly || Sports || [[Rogers Media]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Stitches: The Journal of Medical Humour]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Straight Goods]]'' || || ||English|| || ||  ||\n|-\n|''[[Strategy (magazine)|Strategy]]'' || 1989 || || || || Advertising || [[Brunico Communications]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Style at Home]]'' || 1996 || || English || Monthly || Lifestyle || [[Transcontinental Media]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Swerve (magazine)|Swerve]]'' || 1994 || 2007 ||English|| || LGBT culture, news in Winnipeg ||   ||\n|-\n|''[[Take One (Canadian magazine)|Take One]]'' || 